Former Premier League winger Simon Davies is now playing for a village team in Wales... and will pay £3 to take part in each match. 

Solva FC, an amateur side in Davies' hometown, unveiled the ex-Everton and Tottenham winger as their new marquee signing on Tuesday - but the midfielder will have to pay to play.

The former Wales international only turned 34 in October but has been without a club since leaving Fulham in 2013. 

