Davies was encouraged to join the club by his brother, who is captain of the Welsh side.

Speaking to the South Wales Evening Post, Davies said: 'I'm looking forward to playing a few games with my brother and the friends I started playing with all those years ago. 

Tracey Cole, club secretary at Solva, said: 'It's a big signing for the club.

'I've already told him I'm not paying him - he's going to have to pay subs like everyone else.

'He seems keen and hopefully he'll be available for a few matches.' 

