Starting his career with Peterborough United, Davies moved to Spurs in 2000 but struggled with injuries during his five-year spell at White Hart Lane.

The Welshman moved to Everton following the Toffees' top four finish in 2005 but struggled for form on Merseyside before moving to Fulham in 2007.

Davies spent six years at Craven Cottage and played a key role in Fulham reaching the Europa League final in 2010. The midfielder scored in the semi-final against Hamburg and against Atletico Madrid in the final - which Roy Hodgson's side lost 2-1.

Davies, who earned 58 caps for his country, joined Dean Saunders as a pundit for Sky Sports' coverage of Wales' 2-1 win over Andorra on Tuesday night.

